# Nmap Basics

## Commands Practiced

### Scan a Host
```bash
nmap 192.168.1.1
```

### Scan Specific Ports
```bash
nmap -p 22,80,443 192.168.1.1
```

### Service Detection
```bash
nmap -sV 192.168.1.1
```

### OS Detection
```bash
sudo nmap -O 192.168.1.1
```

